2.19. Specific to corporate cards
:SKRSLUT.
.br
In the case of corporate cards, where the company is held liable for
all claims arising from the issuing and use of the card, the cardholder
will nevertheless be held jointly liable with the company for any
payment claim resulting from the issuing and use of the card:
.br
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
-造if &BANKNAVN. can prove that at the time the card was used, the
cardholder knew or should have known there was an imminent risk that the
company would not be able to pay any debt to &BANKNAVN. thus incurred, or
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
-造if the cardholder has been reported to or registered by the Danish
Business Authority as a member of the board of directors or executive
board, or
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
-造if the cardholder is the owner/co-owner of a personally owned company
including a general partnership, or
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
-造if the card is used to withdraw cash and/or purchase travellers'
cheques, or if the card is used for private purposes - i.e. when the
goods or services in question cannot be considered to have been
acquired in the interests of the company.
.of
