2.20. Changing card terms and conditions
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The card terms and conditions may be changed without notice if the
changes in question benefit you. Changes that do not benefit you may be
made on two months' notice.
.sp 3mm
If the card terms and conditions are changed, you will be informed of this
directly via electronic media or by mail.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the card terms and conditions are changed, you must inform us that
you do not wish to be subject to the new terms and conditions before
they come into effect. If you do not inform us of this, you will be
considered to have accepted the changes.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If you inform the bank that you do not wish to be bound by the new card
terms and conditions, the agreement will be considered to have been
terminated as from the time at which the new card terms and conditions
come into effect.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
2.21. Industrial action
:SKRSLUT.
.br
You cannot use the card in Denmark if &BANKNAVN., NETS and/or the data
centres used by these organisations become involved in industrial
action. Advertisements will be taken out in the daily newspapers
without delay to provide information in connection with the start and
finish of such action.
.kp off
.sp 3mm
.kp on
You cannot expect to be able to use the card outside Denmark if one or
more of &BANKNAVN.'s or NETS's data centres, or if one or more of
NETS's international partners becomes involved in industrial action. In
the event of industrial action exclusively outside Denmark, it will
still be possible to use the card in Denmark.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
